Chinese President Xi Jinping went on an inspection tour of south China's Hainan Province from April 10 to 13. It was his third domestic tour in 2022. During the inspection, Xi called on local officials to take ecological protection as an important task. He also gave instructions on building the Wenchang Spacecraft Launch Site into a world-leading facility, and on accelerating the development of Hainan into a free trade port with Chinese characteristics and global influence.